The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal processing, which are both covered by the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) sub-categories. The paper also proposes an iterative reweighted method, which falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper addresses the issue of discretization in compressed sensing, which is related to numerical analysis and optimization, and thus could fall under the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with applications such as direction-of-arrival (DOA) estimation and line spectral estimation, which are related to statistical inference and estimation, and thus could fall under the cs.SI (Statistics) sub-category.
